description: Delete all 2s, 3s, 5s, 7s from the sequence of nonnegative integers.
references: F. Iacobescu, Smarandache Partition Type and Other Sequences, Bull. Pure Appl. Sciences, Vol. 16E, No. 2 (1997), pp. 237-240.
links: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Smarandache Sequences
F. Smarandache, Sequences of Numbers Involved in Unsolved Problems.
mathematica: t = Table[IntegerDigits[n], {n, 0, 100}]; t2 = Table[Select[t[[i]], ! MemberQ[{2, 3, 5, 7}, #] &], {i, Length[t]}]; t3 = DeleteCases[t2, {}]; FromDigits /@ t3 (* _T. D. Noe_, Oct 18 2011 *)
author: R. Muller
extensions: a(42) corrected and extended by T. D. Noe, Oct 18 2011
